race.comment: Small field for the opener in which a couple of in-form horses appeal. ZOUPURRING (3) is one of those, having won two from three this preparation. His better form has been on the big track but he maps to settle close in the small field and, if he's within striking distance at the 200m, he can win again. Opperman is building a strong association with him. NASHO (5) has been back to the trials after finishing out of the money as favourite last start. He led and won at this track over 1400m two starts back and he'll take some catching again here, especially with 51kg on his back. DANCING STORM (7) never got into the race last start but his prior form was consistent without winning. He looks a top-three chance. The best of MY KHALIFA (2) can give this a shake but it's been a while between wins, while I'M A DEXSTAR (4) can improve into the placings second-up.
